<strong>Connect USB Mouse</strong>
Case ID: hmu-001

This tests that ubuntu can recognise your mouse.
<dl>
    <dt>Remove all USB mice and trackballs connected to the computer 
    <dt>Open Terminal</dt> 
    <dt>Run lsusb in the terminal</dt> 
        <dd>No USB mice should be detected</dd>
    <dt>Connect the USB mouse to the computer</dt> 
    <dt>Run lsusb in the terminal</dt> 
        <dd>The mouse should be detected</dd>
    <dt>Disconnect the mouse from the computer.</dt>
    <dt>Run lsusb again</dt> 
        <dd>The mouse should no longer be detected</dd>
    <dt>Please include your device's model in your feedback</dd>
</dl>


<strong>Test USB Mouse</strong>
Case ID: hmu-002
This tests that the mouse responds normally in Ubuntu.
<dl>
    <dt>Move the mouse. Verify that the mouse cursor moves on screen.</dt>
        <dd>The cursor should move</dd>
    <dt>Right-click on the desktop. Select Create Document â†’ Create Empty File. Title it test.txt</dt>
        <dd>Right- and left-clicking should work</dd>
    <dt>Double-click the test.txt file you created</dt>
        <dd>A text editor should open</dd>
    <dt>Close the text editor</dt>
    <dt>Drag test.txt to the trash can</dt> 
        <dd>The files should drag</dd>
</dl>

